# Core development norms

- Ask for clarification when scope or requirements are unclear.
- Implement only what was discussed; no scaffold or demo code unless asked.
- Preserve existing comments; add comments only for non-obvious logic.
- Match project naming, patterns, and formatter/linter configs.
- Minimal diffs — touch only lines needed for the request.
- Run the layered test gates before commit/push (see `browser-game-testing.mdc`): `check` → headed/ui e2e when UI changes → headless e2e → cross-browser before PR. Execute commands; do not only list them.
- Never paste secrets, API keys, or `.env` contents into chat.
- Do not commit unless the user explicitly asks.
- Agent runs terminal commands (`git`, `npm`, `gh`) — does not only print them.
